In order to get intellij to work with python then following
has to be done:

1. download the pyCharm plugin for intellij
   https://plugins.jetbrains.com/plugin/download?pr=&updateId=27053     //should be compatible with intellij versions 162.1121+ 
2. open intellij python project
3. go to file->project structure->Modules
4. add under python_projects a Python Interpreter --> ref: /usr/bin/python2.7

if python SDK is not in /usr/bin  then download it from here:
https://www.python.org/downloads/

if python in not installed then do followingi (http://askubuntu.com/questions/798123/how-do-i-install-python-3-5-2) :

sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install python3
